http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Hyderabad/Congress-to-open-cell-for-US-bound-students/article13992816.ece

The Congress party is planning to set up a cell here to create awareness about difficulties in pursuing their dreams of higher education in the US to the students planning to go there from the two Telugu States.An awareness meet was conducted in the Andhra Pradesh Congress Committee (APCC) office here which was also attended by leaders from Telangana Pradesh Congress Committee (TPCC) on Sunday on the difficulties being faced by the US-bound students in the recent weeks.Representatives of the NRI wing of Congress and NSUI also participated in the meeting.Speaking at the meeting, APCC president N. Raghuveera Reddy, TPCC working president M. Bhatti Vikramarka, AICC official spokesperson Madhu Yashki, expert on US legal affairs Shandrilya Sharma, NRI cell chairman Vinod and others alleged that the State and Central governments had failed to come to the rescue of students who were deported from the US in the recent week ruining their dream of higher education there.Legal issuesThe Congress party would try to create awareness among such students and bring back light into their lives.Mr. Sharma explained about the legal issues and the precautions to be taken by students planning to study in the US.It will create awareness about difficulties in pursuing dreams of higher education in the US among them